				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It is good they answered this, but I really won't change ANY of my feelings until Questions 1 & 2 at LEAST are answered from our "Letter to Brenlo and the Development Team" are answered.  And preferrably 3-5 as well!
<br />

<br />
Small tweaks like this may not be trivial from a coding perspective, but they are a non-issue balance-wise, as well as for class envy.  It is simply a simplification of the interface.  The REAL issues are what matter.  This doesn't qualify.  If they said we'll give you the answers to 1 and 2 but you'll NEVER get this change, i'd be like "ok, no problem."
<br />

<br />
Answer 1 and 2, followed by 3-5 shortly after.  The rest I could care less about until those are answered, since they are the base of the entire class's role in the game, and if they don't know for EVERY class in the game, then they DEFINITELY shouldn't be raising the level cap, adding more unknown territory.
<br />

<br />
For those who don't remember offhand, the 1-5 re-posted are:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Xalmat wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">1)-What is Sony Online Entertainment's definition of the Magician class and what is our role in solo, group and raid situations? (Example: Mages strength is thru their pet and their pet is second to none their nukes are. their summoning ability is)
<br />

<br />
2)-What is our relative damage rank among all of the "DPS" classes? (Melee/caster: example
<br />

<br />
short term: wizard > magician + pet > rogue > monk ~ ranger ~ berserker? ~ necro? > beastlord? > mage w/o pet ~ druid > warrior ~ shadowknight > paladins (minus Slay Undead) > bard > rest
<br />

<br />
long term (10 minutes +): rogue > necro? > monk ~ ranger~ berserker? ~ mage + pet > beastlord? > the rest)
<br />

<br />
3)-What is our relative damage rank among just the spell caster classes?
<br />

<br />
(Short term, burst fights, wizards > mages > necro.mid term, mages > wizard ~ necro...long term, necro > mages ~ wizard)
<br />

<br />
4)-Are we, the premier pet class? (If so, why are we less capable of supporting our pets as other classes? Example: Why are Magician pet heals so lacking? Why are Dire Charm pets perceived as out-damaging our pets?
<br />

<br />
5)-Are we, or are we not, a soloing class? If we are, why is soloing from level 61 beyond far less viable than it was from levels 1 to 60? Why do many classes (especially classes able to Kite and Quad-Kite) have a superior solo advantage?
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
